ights , united states of America ： Allyn and Bacon A Viacom Company.Klein, J. (1989). K-12 drama/theatre research for the 1990s： An agenda for dramatic action. Design for Arts in Education, 90(9), 26-33.Kostelnik, M. J., Soderman, A. K. & Whiren, A.P. (2004). Developmentally appropriate curriculum ： best practices in early childhood education(3rd).New Jersey ： Pearson Education.Lim, B. (2004) Aesthetic discourses in early childhood settings ： Dewey, Steiner, and Vygotsky. Early Child Development and Care, 174(5), 473-486.McCaslin, N. (1987). Creative drama in the primary grades. Longman.National Center for Education Statistics (1997). The NAEP 1997 Arts Report Card： Eighth-grade finding form the national assessment of educational progress. U.S. Department of education office of Educational Research and Improvement.Queensland Sdudies Authority .(Electroinc version )The Arts (2002) sourcebook modules. Rerieved July 11, 2007, from http://www.qsa.qld.edu.au/syllabus/687.htmlSalisbury, B. (1987). Theatre arts in the elementary school(k-3) and (4-6) . New Orleans ： Anchorage Press.Siks, G. B. (1983). Drama with children(2ed). New York： Harper& Row.Stinson, M. (2008) Planning in drama.Unpublished mnuscripe.The Consortium of National Arts Education Associations. (1994) National standards for arts education ： Dance, music, theatre, visual art. Virginia ： Music Educators National Conference.The Office of the Queensland School Curriculum Council(2002). The arts： Year 1 to 10 sourcebook modules. Austraila.Winston, J. (2007). Drama and beauty： Inspiring the desire to learn. 6th World Congress of International Drama / Theatre and Education Association.: Hong Kong.


